A Virgin Active member at the Melrose Arch branch has tested positive for the coronavirus. The rest of their gyms are still in operation. They've offered members a contract freeze for 30 days. eNCA's Silindelo Masikane is on that story. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Virgin Active South Africa has shut the doors of its Melrose Arch branch after one of the members of the gym tested positive for coronavirus. According to the group, the member has not returned to the gym since 13 March. Members who were at the gym on that day and are displaying symptoms are advised to seek medical attention. READ: Coronavirus In SA: Spreading fake news could land you in jail The gym will reportedly be disinfected before opening its doors again to the public. Meanwhile, the gym is offering members a contract freeze for 30 days.